# =============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES TEMPLATE FOR ZSH/BASH (.env file)
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to ~/.env and fill in your actual values
# This file is sourced in zsh/bash configs for environment setup
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit the actual ~/.env file with real credentials!
# =============================================================================

# ===== USER CONFIGURATION =====
# Used for git config generation and personal setup
USER_FULLNAME="Your Full Name"
USER_EMAIL="your.email@example.com"
PERSONAL_USER="your-username"

# ===== MACHINE TYPE =====
# Set to "pro" for work machines, "perso" for personal machines
PC_TYPE="perso"  # Options: pro | perso

# ===== CUSTOM VARIABLES =====
# Add your own environment variables below

# ===== NOTES =====
# Difference between .env and .envrc:
# - .env: Sourced by shell config, for non-sensitive variables
# - .envrc: Managed by direnv, per-directory, for sensitive secrets
#
# Usage:
# 1. Copy: cp .env.sample ~/.env
# 2. Edit: nvim ~/.env
# 3. Restart shell: exec $SHELL -l
